{
  "texts": [
    "Experimental AnalysesModels and datasets.",
    "We consider a diverse set of LLMs across scale, specialization, and training paradigms.",
    "We evaluate Qwen (3B, 7B): open-weight base models (Bai et al. 2023) employed as non-fine-tuned baselines; G1 (3B, 7B): graphspecialized variants obtained by fine-tuning Qwen with supervised and, then, reinforcement learning (Guo et al.",
    "2025); gpt-oss (20B, 120B) (OpenAI 2025): recently released, larger open-weight models serving to assess scaling effects without task-specific finetuningfoot_0.",
    "Inference temperature is fixed at 0."
  ]
